1️⃣ Go to Microsoft Defender for Cloud
Log in to Azure Portal → Search for Defender for Cloud.
In the Left Menu, go to Workload Protections
Click on Just-In-Time VM Access under Advanced Protection.

2️⃣ Select the VM
Find the VM where JIT is enabled.
Click on the VM Name to open its settings.

3️⃣ Disable JIT Access
Click on the "Edit" button at the top.
Under the JIT configuration, find Port 22 (SSH) or any other ports listed.
Click Remove for each listed port.
Click Save to apply the changes.
